<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="K_5514" type="Brief"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>James Dredge an Alfred Escher, London, Dienstag, 10. Oktober 1871</title></titleStmt><publicationStmt><p>Digitale Briefedition Alfred Escher, Zürich: Alfred Escher-Stiftung.</p></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><msDesc><msIdentifier><institution>SBB Historic</institution><idno>VGB_GB_SBBGB01_008</idno></msIdentifier></msDesc><bibl type="printed"/></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><textClass><keywords scheme="http://briefedition.alfred-escher.ch/keywords"><term>Gotthardbahnprojekt</term><term>Presse (allgemein)</term></keywords></textClass><correspDesc><correspAction type="sent"><persName key="Dredge James" type="addressee">James Dredge</persName><persName key="Escher (vom Glas) Alfred" type="sender">Alfred Escher</persName><placeName>London</placeName><date when="1871-10-10">10. Oktober 1871</date></correspAction><correspContext><ref type="previous" target="B7999"/><ref type="next" target="B8000"/><ref type="next-in-corresp" target="B5515"/></correspContext></correspDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><front>
      
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_5514_p1"> <note type="addendum" xml:id="K_5514_c0">Nachträgliche Notiz oben rechts auf Seite 1 von dritter Hand mit roter Farbe: <orig>1105 (sammt <choice><abbr>Beil.</abbr><expan>Beilage</expan></choice>)</orig>.</note> <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <hi rend="printed">ENGINEERING:
			<lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>AN ILLUSTRATED WEEKLY JOURNAL,
			<lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>Offices, 37, Bedford <choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Street (Strasse)</expan></choice> Strand.</hi>
        </p>
      
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_5514_p2"><lb xml:id="p1-l4"/><hi rend="printed">
            <placeName key="London (UK)">London</placeName>, <choice><abbr>W. C.</abbr><expan>Western Central (westlicher Stadtteil)</expan></choice> </hi>
          <lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>
          <date when="1871-10-10">10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> <hi rend="printed">day of</hi> October <hi rend="printed">187</hi>1</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_5514_p3"><lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>Alfred Escher <choice><abbr>Eoqre</abbr><expan>Eosquire (hochwohlgeboren)</expan></choice> </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_5514_p4"><lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>Dear Sir,
			</p>
      </div>
    </front><body>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_5514_p5"><lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>I venture to trouble
				<lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>you with reference to the great
				<lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>work of the <placeName key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">Saint-Gothard</placeName> railway
				<lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>&amp; tunnel. We are desirous of
				<lb xml:id="p1-l12"/>publishing with as much detail
				<lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>as possible everything relating
				<lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>to this great work which now
				<lb xml:id="p1-l15"/>it would appear will be com<lb xml:id="p1-l16" break="no"/>menced, and I trust that you
				<lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>may be enabled to comply with
				<lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>my request and furnish me
				<lb xml:id="p1-l19"/>with any drawings, statistics
				<pb n="2"/><lb xml:id="p2-l1"/>and report you may have
				<lb xml:id="p2-l2"/>upon the subject. We have
				<lb xml:id="p2-l3"/>already had to thank you
				<lb xml:id="p2-l4"/>for your kind attention to this
				<lb xml:id="p2-l5"/>Journal, &amp; I trust that the pre<lb xml:id="p2-l6" break="no"/>sent request will not be too
				<lb xml:id="p2-l7"/>great a tax upon your com<lb xml:id="p2-l8" break="no"/>plaisance,
			</p>
    </body><back>
      <div type="closer"><p rend="center" xml:id="K_5514_p6"><lb xml:id="p2-l9"/>Yours very truly
			</p> </div>
      <div type="signature">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_5514_p7"><lb xml:id="p2-l10"/>James Dredge</p>
      </div>
    </back></text></TEI>